article.headline: Sacramento State 74, Southern Utah 67
article.story: SACRAMENTO, Calif. (AP) -- Jameel Pugh had 25 points to help Sacramento State beat Southern Utah 74-67 Monday. E.J. Harris and Alex Bausley added 14 and 12 points, respectively, for the Hornets (1-1) who won their home opener after losing to Michigan on the road Saturday. Tim Gainey had 23 points and eight rebounds, and Jason Baker added 10 for the Southern Utah (1-1) who won the Mid-Continent Conference Championship three years ago. Bigger, quicker, and stronger, the Hornets hit seven of their first 10 shots to take a 17-4 lead early in the first half. E. J. Harris scored 11 points, including three 3-point shots in the last 4:10, to give Sacramento State a comfortable 39-21 halftime lead. The Hornets finished the first-half shooting 55 percent from the field. In the second half, Sacramento State built up their margin to 19 points before the Southern Utah came back to cut the lead 69-66 after Curtis Lincoln hit a lay up with 2:03 left. Pugh, who hit four 3-point shots in the second half, hit another one on the next possession to expand Sacramento State's lead to 72-66. The Hornets made two of four free throws in the last 24 seconds to end the game.
